  "text": "A ranula is a cystic lesion in the floor of the mouth, formed either as a retention cyst or pseudocyst as a result of extravasation of mucus in the surrounding tissue [CITATION_1] . It may be treated by micro-marsupialization, marsupialization or excision of lesion with or without the associated salivary gland [CITATION_2] .",
